Package: tardoc
Title: Generate Documentation and Analytics for targets Pipelines
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R: person("Cathal", "Byrne", email = "cathal.byrne@cso.ie", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Auto-generates documentation for targets pipelines across four tiers:
    (1) A self-contained HTML viewer with Fuse.js search and mermaid graphs;
    (2) A DuckDB WASM analytics viewer with full SQL, BM25 search, dplyr syntax,
    and recursive lineage queries — self-contained, opens as file://;
    (3) A Quack-protocol server analytics viewer with BERT semantic search
    (quackformers), FAISS ANN index, function call graph (sitting_duck), and
    git history (duck_tails);
    (4) An LLM chat interface over the pipeline database via ellmer, supporting
    OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama, llama.cpp, and any OpenAI-compatible provider.
    The pipeline database is also exposable as an MCP server (duckdb_mcp) for
    use with Claude Desktop and Claude Code. When llm=TRUE, descriptions are
    auto-generated for undescribed targets and explanations added to function
    pages.
